title: S.J. football: Clayton rally downs Maple Shade
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports "We went to some old-school football, and we just ran the ball."
Senior Tyreek Jackson and junior Devon Carr both logged strong performances, rushing for 135 yards and 95 yards, respectively. The duo combined for three of Clayton's four second-half touchdowns. Carr's standout day came despite his sitting out most of the first half as a coach's decision. 
Five running backs carried the ball for the Clippers, including Nate Garrison, who scored the final touchdown. 
The Clippers improved to 5-1, and will face Gloucester Friday. 
In other WJFL interdivision games: 
Edwin Lopez found the end zone twice for Woodrow Wilson in a 40-0 rout of visiting Schalick. Lopez returned a punt 65 yards for a TD, and later found an opening to score on a 35-yard run. 
Najyere Edwards snapped off a 45-yard touchdown run to put Camden in the lead for good in a 33-13 victory against host Glassboro. Demian Thomas, Brad Hawkins, Dustin Singleton, and Joshua Clark also scored touchdowns on the ground. 
Colonial. Shane Rodriguez's interception return for a touchdown started the scoring for Gateway, and the offense took it from there in a 22-20 win at Audubon. Josh Davis carried the ball 36 times for 162 yards and scored a touchdown on a 48-yard scamper. 
Dashon Burdett ran for 161 yards and three touchdowns, and Collingswood defeated host Woodbury, 42-23. The Panthers ran the ball 48 times for 439 yards.
